> this is your own travis build

My own travis build works. What does not work on your side? The library is created here: https://travis-ci.org/TokTok/jvm-toxcore-c/jobs/173011835#L949.

> why is this so complicated to build?

Because the various platforms we want to support look very different. We've been through several rounds of simplification. I've rewritten the build scripts from scratch at least three times, thinking it doesn't need to be so complicated, but it always turns out to need to handle all kinds of special cases.

> its all errors after the first error

Although it does say "error" a lot, these are actually warnings that are printed to stderr. SBT thinks they are errors, because it has no clue what we're actually executing there.

What is *your* error? Can you post *your* build log? Because mine works.

By the way, you should use the branch I'm trying to pull in #8. The master branch works with irungentoo/toxcore, not with the most recent toktok/toxcore. You need #8 for that. @wiiaam or someone else needs to approve.

This is because you're using master, which not compatible with c-toxcore at the moment. Antox won't build with jvm-toxcore-c, either, because some API changed. I've asked @wiiaam to review the API changes.

You can use jvm-toxcore-c master with c-toxcore 0.0.1 and possibly some later 0.0.x versions. It won't work with 0.1.x.
You can see the API changes here: https://github.com/TokTok/jvm-toxcore-api/pull/1/files.
